<item>
            <title>[HIVE-15529] LLAP: TaskSchedulerService can get stuck when scheduling tasks as disabled node is not re-enabled in NodeEnablerCallable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-15529</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Easier way to simulate the issue:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Start hive cli with &quot;--hiveconf hive.execution.mode=llap&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
2. Run a sql script file (e.g sql script containing tpc-ds queries)&lt;br/&gt;
3. In the middle of the run, press &quot;ctrl+C&quot; which would interrupt the current job. This should not exit the hive cli yet.&lt;br/&gt;
4. After sometime, launch the same SQL script in same cli. This would get stuck indefinitely (waiting for computing the splits).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Even when cli is quit, AM runs forever until explicitly killed. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Issue seems to be around &lt;tt&gt;LlapTaskSchedulerService::schedulePendingTasks&lt;/tt&gt; dealing with the loop when it encounters &lt;tt&gt;DELAYED_RESOURCES&lt;/tt&gt; on task scheduling. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
